<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>day-man • man of the day</xh5><p> <i>day-man—</i>a man who does work during the day or on a day-shift: A company taxi is usually driven by both a <u>dayman</u> and a night-man.</p><p> <i>man of the day—</i>1. an outstanding man of his time: Hamsun was a <u>man of the day</u>, who, despite his age, strove to make his ideal into a reality. <i>Cf.: man of the year</i>—a man who has done the most to influence the events of the particular year (as featured by the U.S. newsmagazine Time): Mikhail Gorbachev was the <u>man of the year</u> for 1987, an eminently defensible choice.... 2. <i>(Military)</i> a soldier on duty for the day: Cooked food was “dished out” by the orderly <u>men of the day</u>.</p> </entry>
